Sentencas: Spray pyrolysis has been used to prepare La-0.6 Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta thin film cathodes for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications.
Titulo: Spray pyrolysis of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ thin film cathodes

Sentencas: The films are polycrystalline with nano-meter sized grains and less than 1 mu m in thickness.
Titulo: Spray pyrolysis of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ thin film cathodes

Sentencas: Deposition parameters for film deposition have been established.
Titulo: Spray pyrolysis of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ thin film cathodes

Sentencas: The ratio of deposition temperature to solvent boiling point is found to be the most important processing parameter that determines whether a crack free homogeneous and coherent film is obtained.
Titulo: Spray pyrolysis of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ thin film cathodes

Sentencas: The morphology can be tailored by the deposition parameters.
Titulo: Spray pyrolysis of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ thin film cathodes

Sentencas: Annealing at 650 degrees C for four hours in air results in coherent films of the desired perovskite phase.
Titulo: Spray pyrolysis of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ thin film cathodes

Sentencas: The films are potential cathodes for thin film micro-solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Spray pyrolysis of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ thin film cathodes
